The '''Sabrashi''' were a group from the [[Sabrash system/Legends|Sabrash system]].<ref name="Planetnamia">{{JCFCite|url=posts/27848315|board=Literature|thread=The Essential Atlas and Galactic Cartography: Official Discussion|user=[[Jason Fry|jasonfry]]|date=2007-12-11|time=7:59 AM|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170916153037/http://boards.theforce.net/threads/the-essential-atlas-and-galactic-cartography-official-discussion.21938930/page-43|quote=I wouldn't get your hopes up re alien homeworlds, beyond simple stuff like the Planetnamian species getting a Planetnamia on the map or things Dan and I can account for with a relatively quick reference.|archivefile=File:JasonFry-JCFAtlasHomeworlds.png}} [[Jason Fry]], co-author of ''[[The Essential Atlas]]'', stated his intention to create homeworlds for numerous species based on context implied from their names. Sabrash appears to be one such case.</ref> They were behind [[Sabrashi Bio-Chemical Deterrents, Inc.]],<ref name="GFT">''[[Galladinium's Fantastic Technology]]''</ref> the developer of the [[FSI-200 Fear Stick/Legends|fear stick]], a potent self-defense weapon that appeared to be a writing [[Stylus/Legends|stylus]].<ref name="TNEFtWaT">''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref>

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
The Sabrashi were first mentioned in [[Galladinium's Fantastic Technology]] in the context of the [[Sabrashi Bio-Chemical Deterrents, Inc.|Sabrashi Bio-Chemical Deterrents]] corporation. They were later referenced in [[Kathy Tyers]]' novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Balance Point]]'' and ''[[The New Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''. None of these sources clarify the nature of the Sabrashi as an organization, a culture, or a [[Species/Legends|species]].

